Simple Test Suite for Paragon

Heavily 'inspired by' the compiler construction course Test Suite.

-----------
  Usage
-----------

To install, run:
  
  ghc -main-is Test --make Test.hs

On Unix, the following commands are available as well:

  make
  make clean

To run all the tests in the 'good' and 'bad' folder, run:

  ./Test  
  
-----------
  Creating new tests
-----------

To create new tests, just add the .para files in the right sub-folder. Note that
the 'bad' ones should also have a corresponding .exp file that prints the 
expected output.
